content:
To search for products that are in stock only, you can add a meta query to your existing code to filter the products based on the `_stock` meta field. Here's an updated `if` block that adds the meta query:
```scss
if ($stock) {
    $args['meta_query'][] = [        'key' => '_stock',        'value' => 0,        'compare' => '>',    ];
}
```
This will filter the products to show only those that have a stock quantity greater than 0.
